# 2. Exercise 1 — Passive RL

## Given episodes (γ = 1, α = 0.1)

### Episode 1

* Cool → Warm (+2)
* Warm → Overheated (−10)

### Episode 2

* Cool → Cool (+2)
* Cool → Warm (+2)
* Warm → Overheated (−10)

---

## 2.1 Monte-Carlo Prediction (Every-Visit)

### Returns

**Episode 1**

* ( v(\text{Cool}) = 2 - 10 = -8 )
* ( v(\text{Warm}) = -10 )

**Episode 2**

* ( v(\text{Cool,1}) = 2 + 2 - 10 = -6 )
* ( v(\text{Cool,2}) = 2 - 10 = -8 )

Average:
[
V(\text{Cool}) = \frac{-8 + (-6) + (-8)}{3} = -7.33
]
[
V(\text{Warm}) = -10
]

---

## 2.2 Incremental Monte-Carlo

Initialization: ( V = 0 )

### Episode 1

* ( V(\text{Cool}) = 0 + 0.1(-8) = -0.8 )
* ( V(\text{Warm}) = 0 + 0.1(-10) = -1.0 )

---

### Episode 2

**Cool returns:**

* ( v_1 = -6,; v_2 = -8 \Rightarrow v = -7 )

Update:

* ( V(\text{Cool}) = -0.8 + 0.1(-7 + 0.8) = -1.42 )

* ( V(\text{Warm}) = -1.0 + 0.1(-10 + 1.0) = -1.9 )

---

## 2.3 TD Prediction

### Episode 1

* Cool:
  [
  V(C) = 0 + 0.1(2 + 0 - 0) = 0.2
  ]

* Warm:
  [
  V(W) = 0 + 0.1(-10) = -1
  ]

---

### Episode 2

* Cool → Cool:
  [
  V(C) = 0.2 + 0.1(2 + 0.2 - 0.2) = 0.4
  ]

* Cool → Warm:
  [
  V(C) = 0.4 + 0.1(2 - 1 - 0.4) = 0.46
  ]

* Warm:
  [
  V(W) = -1 + 0.1(-10) = -1.9
  ]

---

## Final TD values

| State      | Value |
| ---------- | ----- |
| Cool       | 0.46  |
| Warm       | -1.9  |
| Overheated | 0     |

---

# 2.4 Active RL — Q-learning

## Episode 1

* ( Q(C,F) = 0 + 0.1(2) = 0.2 )
* ( Q(W,F) = 0 + 0.1(-10) = -1 )

## Episode 2

* ( Q(C,F) = 0.2 + 0.1(2 + 0.2 - 0.2) = 0.4 )
* ( Q(C,F) = 0.4 + 0.1(2 - 0.4) = 0.56 )
* ( Q(W,F) = -1 + 0.1(-10 + 1) = -1.9 )

---

## Final Q-table

| State      | Slow | Fast |
| ---------- | ---- | ---- |
| Cool       | 0    | 0.56 |
| Warm       | 0    | -1.9 |
| Overheated | 0    | 0    |

---

## Greedy policy

* Cool → Fast
* Warm → Slow

